Inside a rugged stone chamber lit by warm, amber firelight, three large orc-like figures sit around a thick, round wooden table. Their skin is a muted green, their builds massive and muscular, with broad shoulders clad in worn leather and piecemeal metal armor. The central figure stands slightly above the others, positioned at the head of the table, carving into a steaming roast at the center. Their expression is focused, tusks curved and jaw set as the blade sinks into the browned meat.

To the left, another figure leans in, one elbow on the table, gripping a utensil with intense, deliberate concentration. The orc on the right mirrors this posture, more relaxed, watching the carving as they prepare their own plate. The table is crowded with wooden bowls and clay pots brimming with greens, stews, herbs, and rough-hewn loaves. Food spills slightly over the edges, emphasizing abundance and rough hospitality.

Above them, heavy iron pots hang from chains, and shelves carved into the stone walls hold jars, tools, and bundles of dried herbs. Candlelight flickers across the uneven masonry, casting long shadows and revealing the warmth of a fire-lit archway in the background. The atmosphere blends rugged domesticity with an ancient, lived-in sense of place, a moment of communal ritual inside a fortress hall.

Three thick, golden-orange candles rest on a cold windowsill, each flame standing small and steady in the winter dim. The nearest candle is roughly hewn into an irregular cube, its surface veined with delicate, translucent patterns resembling brittle ice or dried honeycomb. Small clusters of crushed, glass-like frost gather around its base. The second candle behind it curves softly at the top, its edges melted into gentle folds. The third, farther back, glows with a warmer, deeper hue, its flame blurring slightly in the shallow focus.

Beside them, the windowpane is coated with condensation and streaks of frost, catching the last light of a fading sunset. Outside, the world is blurred—a wash of pale blue, muted gold, and soft silhouettes—while the reflections of the candle flames shimmer faintly across the glass. The whole scene feels suspended between warmth and cold, each flame a small defiance burning inside a brittle winter hush.
